ly</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~felaar/tal_face2.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Getting a PoA Bridge setup</span><hr size=1> I have gone up to the 7th isle by bridge a couple times now, but being on my LP now I am going to fund a raid there for myself and another guildie who is down to two pieces.  What I'd like to know is how to get a bridge group up there with the least amount of fighting and time, and how much money I'm going to need for stones and coffins.  I personally don't have the time to spend an entire weekend fighting all the way up to the 7th isle.<br>
<br>
Anyone that has setup a SC group there have any suggestions?<br>
<br>
Talenye<br>
 <p><DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:Blur(Add = 1, Direction = 225, Strength = 10)"><h4>Talenye Chath'Zotreth<br>54 Elementalist, Honor Knights, E'ci<br></h4></div><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=182177>Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udurash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Durash</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#333333>(9/30/02 6:21:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1421.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Getting a PoA Bridge setup</span><hr size=1> I've seen it as low as 10k, as high as 50k, generally expect to spend between 5k-7k on stones and coffins (unless you bring an absolutely monstrous group, budget more for that).  <br>
<br>
On DRo, I charge 30k plus expenses to do the bridge.  This is negotiable depending on how well I know the person, and possibly as an item trade.<br>
<br>
